This is a multicentric, randomised, controlled study comparing Laser Iridotomy (LI) to no treatment in subjects with asymptomatic narrow angles (ANA).

One eye of each subject with ANA will be randomised to undergo LI and the other eye will be left alone and will serve as an internal control.

 Subjects are proposed to be followed up once a year for 5 years.

